# Research Logging Rules

This project follows strict research logging rules defined in `rule.md` at the project root.

## Quick reference

Before any run, confirm: track, goal, environment, output folder, baseline vs experiment, varying factor.

After any run, produce: logs, config/command, run note, artifact note(s), issue note (if failure), decision note (if standards changed), sync note.

## Note locations

| Type        | Folder                        | Template                                          |
|-------------|-------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| Run         | `research_log/runs/`          | `research_log/templates/run_template.md`          |
| Experiment  | `research_log/experiments/`   | `research_log/templates/experiment_template.md`   |
| Artifact    | `research_log/artifacts/`     | `research_log/templates/artifact_template.md`     |
| Issue       | `research_log/issues/`        | `research_log/templates/issue_template.md`        |
| Decision    | `research_log/decisions/`     | `research_log/templates/decision_template.md`     |
| Sync note   | `research_log/sync_notes/`    | `research_log/templates/sync_note_template.md`    |

## File naming

- Runs: `YYYY-MM-DD__track__run-type__short-name.md`
- Experiments: `experiment__track__factor__short-name.md`
- Artifacts: `artifact__run-short-name__artifact-type.md`
- Issues: `issue__category__short-name.md`
- Decisions: `decision__short-name.md`
- Sync notes: `sync__YYYY-MM-DD__short-name.md`

## Key constraints

- One factor at a time in controlled experiments.
- Failed runs must still be logged.
- Every baseline change requires a decision note.
- Every result must be reproducible from the run note alone.
- All notes use YAML frontmatter matching the schemas in `rule.md`.

For the full specification, read `rule.md`.
